==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Awl
<hw>Awl</hw> <pr>(⟦add⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>aul</ets>,
<ets>awel</ets>, <ets>al</ets>, AS. <ets>⟦aemac⟧l</ets>,
<ets>awel</ets>; akin to Icel. <ets>alr</ets>, OHG. <ets>⟦amac⟧la</ets>,
G. <ets>ahle</ets>, Lith. <ets>yla</ets>, Skr.
<ets>⟦amac⟧r⟦amac⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>A pointed instrument for piercing
small holes, as in leather or wood; used by shoemakers, saddlers,
cabinetmakers, etc. The blade is differently shaped and pointed for
different uses, as in the <stype>brad awl</stype>, <stype>saddler's
awl</stype>, <stype>shoemaker's awl</stype>, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Awless</ent>⟦br⟧
